  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators propose to perform a double-blind, randomized placebo-controlled trial to
      examine the hypothesis that soy protein with isoflavones could improve glycemic control,
      insulin sensitivity and decrease cardiovascular risk factors in postmenopausal women with
      prediabetes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
